`crates/ctx-verify` is a standalone crate providing both the `ctx-verify` binary implementation (`src/`) and its black-box verification suite (`tests/`). Depending on the crate means depending on `src`'s public surface (`cli::run`, `checks::run_selected`, `runner::Runner`); `tests/` exists purely to hold that surface to its documented contracts and is not itself a dependency target for anything else.

The coupling between `src` and `tests` is one-directional and behavioral, not structural: `tests` fakes `Runner`/`CommandOutcome` to exercise `src`'s check orchestration and CLI rendering without spawning real subprocesses, so any change to `Runner`'s public shape or to `CommandOutcome` ripples into all three test files' fakes. `tests/checks_regen.rs` additionally hardcodes literal argument-list constants mirroring `src/checks/specs.rs`'s regen commands — changing a script path or flag in `specs.rs` requires updating that test file or the regen tests stop testing the real path.

A single invariant is asserted independently in both subtrees and must stay in sync: status precedence `Errored > Fail > Skipped > Pass`, enforced once in `src/model.rs::Report::new` and verified exhaustively (including skip-only → `Skipped`, never `Pass`) across all three test files.

Typical changes start in `src/checks/specs.rs` (new check or regen command) and require a matching update in `tests/checks_regen.rs`'s argument constants and possibly `tests/checks.rs`'s fake keying.

No `intent.md` exists at this level, so no divergence check applies.